Preheat oven to 200 degrees F (95 degrees C). In a medium saucepan bring water and salt to a boil over medium heat. Add butter and stir in potato flakes, onion and cream cheese. Stir in milk until potatoes are soft and fluffy. Spoon into a 9x12 inch casserole dish and top with fried onions. Bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes.